Highly pathogenic avian influenza, Togo
---------------------------------------
Information received on (and dated) 22 Jun 2007 from Dr Batawui Komla
Batasse, directeur de l'elevage et de la peche, Ministere de l'Agriculture
de l'Elevage et de la Peche, Lome, Togo
Report type Immediate notification
Start date 6 Jun 2007
Date of confirmation of event 15 Jun 2007
Date submitted to OIE 25 Jun 2007
Reason for notification: 1st occurrence of a listed disease
Manifestation of disease: clinical disease
Causal agent: highly pathogenic avian influenza virus
Serotype: H5N1
Nature of diagnosis: clinical, laboratory (basic), necropsy
Report pertains to: entire country
Outbreak 1 Sigbehoue, Lacs, Region Maritime
Date of start of outbreak: 6 Jun 2007
Outbreak status: continuing (or date resolved not submitted)
Epidemiological unit: farm
Species: birds
Susceptible 5574
Cases 2505
Deaths 2505
Destroyed 3069
Slaughtered 0
Affected population: hens in an intensive system of farming
Summary of outbreaks
Total outbreaks: 1
Outbreak statistics
Species birds
Apparent morbidity rate 45 per cent
Apparent mortality rate 45 per cent
Apparent case fatality rate 100 per cent
Proportion susceptible removed*100 per cent
* Birds removed from the susceptible population either through death,
destruction, or slaughter
Epidemiology: Source of infection Unknown or inconclusive
Laboratory name and type: Accra Veterinary Laboratory (Ghana) (OIE's
Reference Laboratory)
Species: birds
Test: RT-PCR (reverse transcriptase polymerase chain reaction)
Test date: 22 Jun 2007
Result: positive
Species: birds
Test: rapid tests
Test date: 15 Jun 2007
Result: positive
Species: birds
Test: viral sequencing
Test: date pending
Result: pending
Laboratory name and type: Padova (Italy) (OIE's Reference Laboratory)
Species: birds
Test: RT-PCR
Test date: 22 Jun 2007
Result: positive
Species: birds
Test: rapid tests
Test date: 15 Jun 2007
Result: positive
Species: birds
Test: viral sequencing
Test date: pending
Result: pending
