Highly pathogenic avian influenza, Ghana
----------------------------------------
Information received on (and dated) 21 Jun 2007 from Mr Mensah
Agyen-Frempong, Ministry of Food and Agriculture, director, Veterinary
Services Department, ACCRA, Ghana
Report type: follow-up report No. 7
Start date: 14 Apr 2007
Date of confirmation of event: 28 Apr 2007
Date submitted to OIE: 21 Jun 2007
Reason for notification: 1st occurrence of a listed disease
Manifestation of disease: clinical disease
Causal agent: highly pathogenic avian influenza virus type A
Serotype: H5N1
Nature of diagnosis: suspicion, clinical, laboratory (basic), necropsy
Report pertains to: entire country
Outbreak 1 Aflao, Ketu, Volta
Date of start of outbreak: 13 Jun 2007
Outbreak status: continuing (or date resolved not submitted)
Epidemiological unit: farm
Species: birds
Susceptible 1450
Cases 350
Deaths 350
Destroyed 1100
Slaughtered 0
Affected population: layers under an intensive system of management
Summary of outbreaks
Total outbreaks: 1
Outbreak statistics
Species Birds
Apparent morbidity rate 24 per cent
Apparent mortality rate 24 per cent
Apparent case fatality rate 100 per cent
Proportion susceptible removed *100 per cent
* Removed from the susceptible population either through death, destruction
or slaughter
Epidemiology: source of infection unknown or inconclusive
Epidemiological comments: samples are being prepared for submission to the
OIE Reference Laboratory in Padova (Italy)
Laboratory name and type: Accra veterinary laboratory (National laboratory)
Species: birds
Test: hemagglutination (HA) test
Test date: 19 Jun 2007
Result: positive
Species: birds
Test: rapid tests
Test date: 18 Jun 2007
Result: positive
Laboratory name and type: Noguchi Memorial Institute for Medical Research
(National laboratory)
Species: birds
Test: hemagglutination inhibition test (HIT)
Test date: 20 Jun 2007
Result: positive
